  "canonical_term": "Commodities",
  "aliases": [],
  "school": "General",
  "definition": "A tradable asset class representing physical goods such as metals (gold, oil), energy, and agricultural products (coffee, corn). Known for good volatility, inflation protection, and use as a hedge, but market movements are complex due to many external factors.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Determine if the asset is a physical raw material or primary agricultural product (e.g., gold, crude oil, coffee beans, corn)."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Commodities offer good volatility for trading and serve as inflation protection or a hedging tool. However, their price movements are hard to understand due to many external factors like geopolitics and supply/demand shifts, requiring careful analysis.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Assuming commodity prices are easy to predict without considering external factors."
  ],
